==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Premier
<hw>Pre"mi*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>premier</ets>, fr. L. <ets>primarius</ets> of the first rank,
principal, fr. <ets>primus</ets> the first. See <er>Primary</er>,
<er>Prime</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>First; chief;
principal; <as>as, the <ex>premier</ex> place; <ex>premier</ex>
minister.</as></def> <rj><au>Camden. Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Most ancient; -- said of the peer bearing the oldest
title of his degree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Premier</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Premier
<hw>Pre"mi*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The first minister
of state; the prime minister.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Premiere</ent>⟦br⟧
